-- Polish Stocks: Grupa Lotos, Magellan Shares Move in Warsaw
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i   a n d   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 2012-04-17T16:12:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-17/polish-stocks-grupa-lotos-magellan-shares-move-in-warsaw.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  advanced for a
second day, up 0.9 percent to 2,271.20 in Warsaw.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Warsaw Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  , the country’s second-largest
refiner, jumped 5.7 percent to 30.43 zloty, the highest level in
more than seven months, after oil climbed as Spain’s bond
auction eased concern Europe’s credit crisis will spread and
endanger economic growth.  Magellan SA (MAG)  , a Polish money lender to the health-
care industry, surged 4 percent to 44 zloty, the highest in more
than four years, after Bank Zachodni WBK SA recommended buying
its shares.  To contact the reporters on this story:
